    {
      "block_id": "1d64750c-f3ba-8086-8bc9-fc11886312ad",
      "heading": "Abstract",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Theoretical Grounding",
          "Features",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Groups Created",
          "Cluster Description",
          "Implications",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Problem-Based Learning",
          "104 4th year students",
          "1 Online Course in Social Work and Problem-Solving",
          "Student Reports, Discussion Forums, LMS logs, Questionnaires",
          "None Specified",
          "[RF-IDF OR W2V OR D2V]",
          "Data was collected from Online Discussion Forums in 2020 and 2021 and each post was subsequently encoded as either relevant for course or not relevant. \n\nDiscussion posts themselves were encoded using different NLP techniques: TF-IDF, Word2Vec & Doc2Vec.",
          "Random Forest, SVM, LSTM",
          "{AUC: 0.880 - SVM D2V, Cohen’s Kappa: 0.816 - SVM D2V}",
          "4",
          "Relçevant messages were labelled into 4 PBL-steps:\n\nRepresentation-Relevant, Solution-Relevant, Justification-relevant & Evaluation-relevant",
          "Students are more likely to engage in discussion in discussion with their peers than any other activity (i.e. answering questions). Educators hsould make an effort in fostering an environment where helping peers is rewarded. ",
          "Participation of study was voluntary.\n\nML models ware meant to measure whether a specific forum entry is relevant or irrelevant for the course → which can be used as a hallmark of engagement of procrastinatory behavior. \n\nThe predictions of this model are subsequently used as inputs for the Hierarchical Linear Regression. ",
          "Selection bias → only includes learners who have signed in to participate in a specific course.\n\nSmall sample size (student-wise and number of courses-wise) should be addressed in future works.  \n\n\n "
        ],
        [
          "Regression",
          "Higher Education",
          "Problem-Based Learning",
          "104 4th year students",
          "1 Online Course in Social Work and Problem-Solving",
          "Student Reports, Discussion Forums, LMS logs, Questionnaires",
          "None Specified",
          "[Gender, Prior Knowledge, Self-Regulation, Posted, Replied, Words, Representation-rlvt, Solution-rlvt, Justification-rlvt, Evaluation-rlvt]",
          "The predictions of the ML classifiers are used as features for this model. \n\nThe idea is to identify which steps or phases of the PBL process are relevant towards better performance.",
          "Hierarchical Linear Regression",
          "{Adjsuted R-Squared: 0.682 - Regression using all features, R-Squared: 0.713 - Al Features}",
          "-",
          " Results show that the predictions obtained from the ML models are better representations of peer-learning than exclusively using logs. \n\nSelf-Regulation and peer-learning variables were found to be relevant predictors of PBL performance.",
          "Adequate labelling consistency from human evaluators may contribute to creating models able to predict engagement. \n\nMulti-modal learning analytics may be used to keep track of the stages of the PBL proces learners are into and provide adequate supoport to them.\n\n",
          "Hierarchical linear regression results show that the addition of the peer-learning variables obtained from training the different ML models results into better overall predictions of performance in PBL than common constructs such as prior knowledge or gender. ",
          "Selection bias → only includes learners who have signed in to participate.Small sample size (student-wise and number of courses-wise) should be addressed in future works.   "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
