    {
      "id": "1ad4750c-f3ba-80be-8c82-cd8605594f08",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Multimodal learning analytics has garnered a lot of interest among Problem-Based Learning researchers. Within this context, there is a gap in using text data generated from learner interactions with their peers. The authors explor MMLA on a sample of 104 fourth-year students to classify text in online discussions. Self-Regulation, messages and engagement were found to be predictive of online PBL performance. ",
